# Load the dataset
file_path = '/kaggle/input/beijing-multi-site-air-quality-data/Beijing Multisite air Quality data.csv'
df = pd.read_csv(file_path)

# Display basic information
print("Dataset loaded successfully!")
print(f"\nShape of the dataset: {df.shape} (rows, columns)")
print(f"\nNumber of records (rows): {df.shape[0]}")
print(f"Number of features (columns): {df.shape[1]}")
# Display first 5 records
print("\nFirst 5 records of the dataset:")
print(df.head())

# Display basic statistics
print("\nBasic statistics of numerical columns:")
print(df.describe())

# Check data types and null values
print("\nData types and null values:")
print(df.info())
# Check for missing values before handling
print("\nMissing values before handling:")
print(df.isnull().sum())

# Fill missing values (using forward fill for time series data)
df.fillna(method='ffill', inplace=True)
df.fillna(method='bfill', inplace=True)  # For any remaining NA at start

# Check after handling
print("\nMissing values after handling:")
print(df.isnull().sum().sum(), "missing values remaining")

# Show sample before and after
sample_col = df.columns[df.isnull().any()].tolist()
if sample_col:
    print("\nSample before and after filling (first occurrence):")
    sample_idx = df[sample_col[0]].isnull().idxmax()
    print("Before:")
    print(df.loc[sample_idx-2:sample_idx+2, sample_col[0]])
    print("\nAfter:")
    print(df.loc[sample_idx-2:sample_idx+2, sample_col[0]].fillna(method='ffill'))
else:
    print("\nNo missing values found in the dataset")
    # Check if datetime column exists and convert
if 'date' in df.columns or 'time' in df.columns:
    datetime_col = [col for col in df.columns if 'date' in col.lower() or 'time' in col.lower()]
    if datetime_col:
        print(f"\nConverting datetime column: {datetime_col[0]}")
        df[datetime_col[0]] = pd.to_datetime(df[datetime_col[0]])
        print("Sample after conversion:")
        print(df[datetime_col[0]].head())
    else:
        print("\nNo datetime column found")
else:
    print("\nNo obvious datetime column found in the dataset")
    # Check for categorical variables
categorical_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns.tolist()
if 'station' in df.columns:
    categorical_cols.append('station')

if categorical_cols:
    print("\nCategorical variables found:")
    print(categorical_cols)
    
    # Example: One-hot encoding for station if exists
    if 'station' in categorical_cols:
        print("\nBefore encoding 'station':")
        print(df['station'].value_counts().head())
        
        # One-hot encode
        df = pd.get_dummies(df, columns=['station'], prefix='station')
        
        print("\nAfter encoding (showing new columns):")
        print(df.filter(like='station_').head())
else:
    print("\nNo categorical variables found")
    # For numerical columns (example with PM2.5 if exists)
if 'PM2.5' in df.columns:
    print("\nOutlier analysis for PM2.5:")
    Q1 = df['PM2.5'].quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = df['PM2.5'].quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    
    print(f"Q1: {Q1}, Q3: {Q3}, IQR: {IQR}")
    lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
    
    outliers = df[(df['PM2.5'] < lower_bound) | (df['PM2.5'] > upper_bound)]
    print(f"Number of outliers detected: {len(outliers)}")
    
    # Cap the outliers
    df['PM2.5'] = df['PM2.5'].clip(lower_bound, upper_bound)
    print("\nAfter capping outliers:")
    print(df['PM2.5'].describe())
    # Display final dataset information
print("\nFinal dataset information:")
print(f"Shape: {df.shape}")
print("\nFirst 5 records after preprocessing:")
print(df.head())

print("\nData types after preprocessing:")
print(df.dtypes)

print("\nMissing values after all preprocessing:")
print(df.isnull().sum().sum(), "missing values remaining")
# Save the preprocessed data
output_path = '/kaggle/working/beijing_air_quality_preprocessed.csv'
df.to_csv(output_path, index=False)
print(f"\nPreprocessed data saved to: {output_path}")

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

# Load the preprocessed data
preprocessed_path = '/kaggle/working/beijing_air_quality_preprocessed.csv'
df = pd.read_csv(preprocessed_path)

print("Preprocessed data loaded successfully!")
print(f"\nShape of the dataset: {df.shape} (rows, columns)")

## 1. Basic Data Quality Checks

# Check first few records
print("\nFirst 5 records of preprocessed data:")
print(df.head())

# Check data types
print("\nData types:")
print(df.dtypes)

# Check for missing values
print("\nMissing values count:")
print(df.isnull().sum())

# Check for duplicates
print(f"\nNumber of duplicate rows: {df.duplicated().sum()}")

## 2. Statistical Quality Checks

# Basic statistics
print("\nBasic statistics:")
print(df.describe())

# Check for zeros in numerical columns (might indicate problems)
numerical_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns
print("\nZero values in numerical columns:")
for col in numerical_cols:
    zero_count = (df[col] == 0).sum()
    if zero_count > 0:
        print(f"{col}: {zero_count} zeros ({zero_count/len(df)*100:.2f}%)")

## 3. Temporal Data Checks (if datetime column exists)

datetime_cols = [col for col in df.columns if 'date' in col.lower() or 'time' in col.lower()]
if datetime_cols:
    print("\nTemporal data checks:")
    # Convert to datetime if not already
    df[datetime_cols[0]] = pd.to_datetime(df[datetime_cols[0]])
    
    # Check time range
    print(f"Time range: {df[datetime_cols[0]].min()} to {df[datetime_cols[0]].max()}")
    
    # Check for time gaps
    time_diff = df[datetime_cols[0]].diff().value_counts()
    print("\nTime differences between records:")
    print(time_diff.head())
else:
    print("\nNo datetime column found for temporal checks")

## 4. Categorical Data Checks

categorical_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['object', 'category']).columns
if len(categorical_cols) > 0:
    print("\nCategorical data checks:")
    for col in categorical_cols:
        print(f"\nColumn: {col}")
        print("Unique values:", df[col].nunique())
        print("Value counts:")
        print(df[col].value_counts().head())
else:
    print("\nNo categorical columns found")

## 5. Outlier Checks

if len(numerical_cols) > 0:
    print("\nOutlier checks (using IQR method):")
    for col in numerical_cols:
        Q1 = df[col].quantile(0.25)
        Q3 = df[col].quantile(0.75)
        IQR = Q3 - Q1
        lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
        upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
        
        outliers = df[(df[col] < lower_bound) | (df[col] > upper_bound)]
        print(f"{col}: {len(outliers)} potential outliers ({len(outliers)/len(df)*100:.2f}%)")
else:
    print("\nNo numerical columns for outlier checks")

## 6. Save Quality Report

# Calculate outliers count for each numerical column
outliers_info = {}
if len(numerical_cols) > 0:
    for col in numerical_cols:
        Q1 = df[col].quantile(0.25)
        Q3 = df[col].quantile(0.75)
        IQR = Q3 - Q1
        lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
        upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
        outliers_count = ((df[col] < lower_bound) | (df[col] > upper_bound)).sum()
        outliers_info[col] = outliers_count

quality_report = f"""
DATA QUALITY REPORT
===================
Dataset: {preprocessed_path}
Shape: {df.shape}
Total records: {len(df)}
Total features: {len(df.columns)}

MISSING VALUES
--------------
{df.isnull().sum().to_string()}

DUPLICATES
----------
{df.duplicated().sum()} duplicate rows found

TEMPORAL DATA
-------------
{df[datetime_cols[0]].describe() if datetime_cols else "No datetime column"}

OUTLIERS (IQR METHOD)
--------------------
{outliers_info if len(numerical_cols) > 0 else "No numerical columns"}
"""

report_path = '/kaggle/working/data_quality_report.txt'
with open(report_path, 'w') as f:
    f.write(quality_report)

print(f"\nData quality report saved to: {report_path}")

class DataProcessor:
    def __init__(self, file_path):
        self.file_path = file_path
        self.df = None
        self.quality_report = {}
    
    def load_and_assess_quality(self):
        """Load data and perform comprehensive quality assessment"""
        print("\n1. LOADING DATA AND QUALITY ASSESSMENT")
        print("-" * 50)
        
        # Load data
        self.df = pd.read_csv(self.file_path)
        print(f"Data loaded: {self.df.shape} (rows, columns)")
        
        # Basic quality checks
        print(f"Memory usage: {self.df.memory_usage(deep=True).sum() / 1024**2:.2f} MB")
        print(f"Missing values: {self.df.isnull().sum().sum()}")
        print(f"Duplicate rows: {self.df.duplicated().sum()}")
        
        # Data types assessment
        numerical_cols = self.df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns
        categorical_cols = self.df.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns
        
        print(f"Numerical columns: {len(numerical_cols)}")
        print(f"Categorical columns: {len(categorical_cols)}")
        
        # Store quality metrics
        self.quality_report = {
            'total_rows': int(len(self.df)),
            'total_columns': int(len(self.df.columns)),
            'missing_values': int(self.df.isnull().sum().sum()),
            'duplicates': int(self.df.duplicated().sum()),
            'numerical_cols': int(len(numerical_cols)),
            'categorical_cols': int(len(categorical_cols))
        }
        
        return self.df
    
    def preprocess_data(self):
        """Clean and preprocess the data"""
        print("\n2. DATA PREPROCESSING")
        print("-" * 50)
        
        # Handle wind direction conversion
        if 'wd' in self.df.columns:
            wind_directions = {
                'N':0, 'NNE':22.5, 'NE':45, 'ENE':67.5, 'E':90, 'ESE':112.5,
                'SE':135, 'SSE':157.5, 'S':180, 'SSW':202.5, 'SW':225, 'WSW':247.5,
                'W':270, 'WNW':292.5, 'NW':315, 'NNW':337.5
            }
            self.df['wd'] = self.df['wd'].map(wind_directions)
            print("Wind direction converted to numerical values")
        
        # Handle missing values
        initial_missing = self.df.isnull().sum().sum()
        self.df = self.df.fillna(self.df.mean(numeric_only=True))
        final_missing = self.df.isnull().sum().sum()
        print(f"Missing values handled: {initial_missing} -> {final_missing}")
        
        # Remove duplicates
        initial_rows = len(self.df)
        self.df = self.df.drop_duplicates()
        final_rows = len(self.df)
        print(f"Duplicates removed: {initial_rows} -> {final_rows} rows")
        
        return self.df

class FeatureEngineer:
    def __init__(self, df):
        self.df = df.copy()
    
    def create_features(self):
        """Create advanced features for better model performance"""
        print("\n3. ENHANCED FEATURE ENGINEERING")
        print("-" * 50)
        
        # Temporal features
        if all(col in self.df.columns for col in ['year', 'month', 'day', 'hour']):
            self.df['hour_sin'] = np.sin(2 * np.pi * self.df['hour'] / 24)
            self.df['hour_cos'] = np.cos(2 * np.pi * self.df['hour'] / 24)
            self.df['month_sin'] = np.sin(2 * np.pi * (self.df['month']-1) / 12)
            self.df['month_cos'] = np.cos(2 * np.pi * (self.df['month']-1) / 12)
            
            # Season encoding
            self.df['season'] = self.df['month'].map({12:0, 1:0, 2:0, 3:1, 4:1, 5:1, 
                                                    6:2, 7:2, 8:2, 9:3, 10:3, 11:3})
            
            # Time of day encoding
            self.df['time_of_day'] = pd.cut(self.df['hour'], 
                                          bins=[0, 6, 12, 18, 24], 
                                          labels=[0, 1, 2, 3], 
                                          include_lowest=True).astype(int)
            print("Enhanced temporal features created")
        
        # Meteorological indices
        if all(col in self.df.columns for col in ['DEWP', 'TEMP']):
            self.df['humidity_index'] = self.df['DEWP'] / (self.df['TEMP'] + 1e-6)
            self.df['temp_dewp_diff'] = self.df['TEMP'] - self.df['DEWP']
            print("Meteorological indices created")
        
        # Pollution ratios and interactions
        if all(col in self.df.columns for col in ['PM2.5', 'PM10']):
            self.df['PM_ratio'] = self.df['PM2.5'] / (self.df['PM10'] + 1e-6)
            
        if all(col in self.df.columns for col in ['NO2', 'SO2']):
            self.df['NO2_SO2_ratio'] = self.df['NO2'] / (self.df['SO2'] + 1e-6)
            
        if all(col in self.df.columns for col in ['CO', 'O3']):
            self.df['CO_O3_interaction'] = self.df['CO'] * self.df['O3']
        
        # Enhanced lag features
        for lag in [1, 6, 12, 24, 48]:
            if 'PM2.5' in self.df.columns:
                self.df[f'PM2.5_lag_{lag}'] = self.df['PM2.5'].shift(lag)
            if 'TEMP' in self.df.columns:
                self.df[f'TEMP_lag_{lag}'] = self.df['TEMP'].shift(lag)
            if 'PRES' in self.df.columns:
                self.df[f'PRES_lag_{lag}'] = self.df['PRES'].shift(lag)
        
        # Enhanced rolling statistics
        if 'PM2.5' in self.df.columns:
            for window in [6, 12, 24]:
                self.df[f'PM2.5_roll_mean_{window}'] = self.df['PM2.5'].rolling(window=window).mean()
                self.df[f'PM2.5_roll_std_{window}'] = self.df['PM2.5'].rolling(window=window).std()
                self.df[f'PM2.5_roll_max_{window}'] = self.df['PM2.5'].rolling(window=window).max()
                self.df[f'PM2.5_roll_min_{window}'] = self.df['PM2.5'].rolling(window=window).min()
            print("Enhanced rolling statistics created")
        
        # Wind components and meteorological combinations
        if all(col in self.df.columns for col in ['WSPM', 'wd']):
            self.df['wind_u'] = self.df['WSPM'] * np.sin(np.radians(self.df['wd']))
            self.df['wind_v'] = self.df['WSPM'] * np.cos(np.radians(self.df['wd']))
            
        # Pressure-temperature interaction
        if all(col in self.df.columns for col in ['PRES', 'TEMP']):
            self.df['pres_temp_interaction'] = self.df['PRES'] * self.df['TEMP']
        
        # Clean infinite values
        self.df = self.df.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan)
        self.df = self.df.fillna(self.df.mean(numeric_only=True))
        
        # Drop rows with remaining NaN values
        initial_rows = len(self.df)
        self.df = self.df.dropna()
        final_rows = len(self.df)
        print(f"Final cleaning: {initial_rows} -> {final_rows} rows")
        print(f"Total features created: {len(self.df.columns)}")
        
        return self.df

# 3. ENHANCED MODEL IMPLEMENTATIONS WITH FEATURE IMPORTANCE

class EnhancedModelTrainer:
    def __init__(self, X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test):
        self.X_train = X_train
        self.X_test = X_test
        self.y_train = y_train
        self.y_test = y_test
        self.models = {}
        self.predictions = {}
        self.metrics = {}
        self.feature_importance = {}
        self.training_history = {}
        
        # Store test targets for visualization
        self.test_targets = {}
        self.test_targets['Random Forest'] = y_test.values
        self.test_targets['XGBoost'] = y_test.values
    
    def train_random_forest(self):
        """Train Random Forest model with enhanced parameters"""
        print("\n4.1 TRAINING RANDOM FOREST")
        print("-" * 30)
        
        rf_model = RandomForestRegressor(
            n_estimators=200,
            max_depth=15,
            min_samples_split=5,
            min_samples_leaf=2,
            max_features='sqrt',
            bootstrap=True,
            random_state=42,
            n_jobs=-1
        )
        
        rf_model.fit(self.X_train, self.y_train)
        rf_pred = rf_model.predict(self.X_test)
        
        # Calculate metrics (removed MAPE)
        rf_metrics = {
            'MAE': float(mean_absolute_error(self.y_test, rf_pred)),
            'RMSE': float(np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(self.y_test, rf_pred))),
            'R2': float(r2_score(self.y_test, rf_pred))
        }
        
        # Feature importance
        rf_importance = pd.DataFrame({
            'feature': self.X_train.columns,
            'importance': rf_model.feature_importances_,
            'rank': range(1, len(self.X_train.columns) + 1)
        }).sort_values('importance', ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)
        rf_importance['rank'] = range(1, len(rf_importance) + 1)
        
        print(f"Random Forest trained with {rf_model.n_estimators} trees")
        print(f"  MAE: {rf_metrics['MAE']:.3f}")
        print(f"  RMSE: {rf_metrics['RMSE']:.3f}")
        print(f"  R2: {rf_metrics['R2']:.3f}")
        
        self.models['Random Forest'] = rf_model
        self.predictions['Random Forest'] = rf_pred
        self.metrics['Random Forest'] = rf_metrics
        self.feature_importance['Random Forest'] = rf_importance
        
        return rf_model, rf_pred, rf_metrics
    
    def train_xgboost(self):
        """Train XGBoost model with enhanced parameters"""
        print("\n4.2 TRAINING XGBOOST")
        print("-" * 30)
        
        xgb_model = xgb.XGBRegressor(
            n_estimators=200,
            max_depth=8,
            learning_rate=0.05,
            subsample=0.8,
            colsample_bytree=0.8,
            reg_alpha=0.1,
            reg_lambda=0.1,
            random_state=42,
            n_jobs=-1
        )
        
        # Train with validation set for early stopping
        eval_set = [(self.X_test, self.y_test)]
        xgb_model.fit(
            self.X_train, self.y_train,
            eval_set=eval_set,
            early_stopping_rounds=20,
            verbose=False
        )
        
        xgb_pred = xgb_model.predict(self.X_test)
        
        # Calculate metrics (removed MAPE)
        xgb_metrics = {
            'MAE': float(mean_absolute_error(self.y_test, xgb_pred)),
            'RMSE': float(np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(self.y_test, xgb_pred))),
            'R2': float(r2_score(self.y_test, xgb_pred))
        }
        
        # Feature importance
        xgb_importance = pd.DataFrame({
            'feature': self.X_train.columns,
            'importance': xgb_model.feature_importances_,
            'rank': range(1, len(self.X_train.columns) + 1)
        }).sort_values('importance', ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)
        xgb_importance['rank'] = range(1, len(xgb_importance) + 1)
        
        print(f"XGBoost trained with early stopping")
        print(f"  MAE: {xgb_metrics['MAE']:.3f}")
        print(f"  RMSE: {xgb_metrics['RMSE']:.3f}")
        print(f"  R2: {xgb_metrics['R2']:.3f}")
        
        self.models['XGBoost'] = xgb_model
        self.predictions['XGBoost'] = xgb_pred
        self.metrics['XGBoost'] = xgb_metrics
        self.feature_importance['XGBoost'] = xgb_importance
        
        return xgb_model, xgb_pred, xgb_metrics
    
    def calculate_lstm_feature_importance(self, model, X_test_scaled, y_test_seq, feature_names):
        """Calculate LSTM feature importance using permutation importance"""
        print("  Calculating LSTM feature importance...")
        
        # Get baseline predictions
        baseline_pred = model.predict(X_test_scaled)
        baseline_loss = mean_squared_error(y_test_seq, baseline_pred.flatten())
        
        importance_scores = []
        
        for i, feature in enumerate(feature_names):
            # Create permuted data
            X_permuted = X_test_scaled.copy()
            
            # Permute feature across all timesteps
            for t in range(X_permuted.shape[1]):
                np.random.shuffle(X_permuted[:, t, i])
            
            # Calculate loss with permuted feature
            permuted_pred = model.predict(X_permuted)
            permuted_loss = mean_squared_error(y_test_seq, permuted_pred.flatten())
            
            # Importance is the increase in loss
            importance = permuted_loss - baseline_loss
            importance_scores.append(max(0, importance))  # Only positive importance
        
        # Create importance dataframe
        lstm_importance = pd.DataFrame({
            'feature': feature_names,
            'importance': importance_scores,
            'rank': range(1, len(feature_names) + 1)
        }).sort_values('importance', ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)
        lstm_importance['rank'] = range(1, len(lstm_importance) + 1)
        
        return lstm_importance
    
    def train_lstm(self, epochs=30):
        """Train LSTM model with enhanced architecture and feature importance"""
        print(f"\n4.3 TRAINING LSTM (epochs={epochs})")
        print("-" * 30)
        
        # Scale the data
        scaler = MinMaxScaler()
        X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(self.X_train)
        X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(self.X_test)
        
        # Create sequences for LSTM
        def create_sequences(X, y, seq_length=24):
            X_seq, y_seq = [], []
            for i in range(len(X) - seq_length):
                X_seq.append(X[i:i+seq_length])
                y_seq.append(y[i+seq_length])
            return np.array(X_seq), np.array(y_seq)
        
        seq_length = min(24, len(X_train_scaled) // 10)
        X_train_seq, y_train_seq = create_sequences(X_train_scaled, self.y_train.values, seq_length)
        X_test_seq, y_test_seq = create_sequences(X_test_scaled, self.y_test.values, seq_length)
        
        print(f"  Sequence length: {seq_length}")
        print(f"  Training sequences: {X_train_seq.shape}")
        print(f"  Test sequences: {X_test_seq.shape}")
        
        # Build enhanced LSTM model
        lstm_model = Sequential([
            LSTM(64, return_sequences=True, input_shape=(seq_length, X_train_scaled.shape[1])),
            Dropout(0.2),
            LSTM(32, return_sequences=True),
            Dropout(0.2),
            LSTM(16),
            Dropout(0.1),
            Dense(32, activation='relu'),
            Dense(16, activation='relu'),
            Dense(1)
        ])
        
        # Compile with optimized settings
        optimizer = Adam(learning_rate=0.001)
        lstm_model.compile(optimizer=optimizer, loss='mse', metrics=['mae'])
        
        print(f"  Model architecture: {lstm_model.count_params()} parameters")
        
        # Enhanced callbacks
        early_stopping = EarlyStopping(
            monitor='val_loss',
            patience=10,
            restore_best_weights=True,
            verbose=1
        )
        
        reduce_lr = ReduceLROnPlateau(
            monitor='val_loss',
            factor=0.5,
            patience=5,
            min_lr=0.0001,
            verbose=1
        )
        
        # Train model with clear epoch tracking
        print(f"  Starting training for {epochs} epochs...")
        history = lstm_model.fit(
            X_train_seq, y_train_seq,
            epochs=epochs,
            batch_size=32,
            validation_split=0.2,
            callbacks=[early_stopping, reduce_lr],
            verbose=1
        )
        
        # Store training history with proper conversion
        self.training_history['LSTM'] = {
            'loss': [float(x) for x in history.history['loss']],
            'val_loss': [float(x) for x in history.history['val_loss']],
            'mae': [float(x) for x in history.history['mae']],
            'val_mae': [float(x) for x in history.history['val_mae']],
            'epochs_trained': int(len(history.history['loss'])),
            'best_epoch': int(np.argmin(history.history['val_loss']) + 1)
        }
        
        print(f"  Training completed in {len(history.history['loss'])} epochs")
        print(f"  Best epoch: {np.argmin(history.history['val_loss']) + 1}")
        
        # Predictions
        lstm_pred = lstm_model.predict(X_test_seq, verbose=0).flatten()
        
        # Calculate metrics (removed MAPE)
        lstm_metrics = {
            'MAE': float(mean_absolute_error(y_test_seq, lstm_pred)),
            'RMSE': float(np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test_seq, lstm_pred))),
            'R2': float(r2_score(y_test_seq, lstm_pred))
        }
        
        print(f"  MAE: {lstm_metrics['MAE']:.3f}")
        print(f"  RMSE: {lstm_metrics['RMSE']:.3f}")
        print(f"  R2: {lstm_metrics['R2']:.3f}")
        
        # Calculate feature importance
        lstm_importance = self.calculate_lstm_feature_importance(
            lstm_model, X_test_seq, y_test_seq, self.X_train.columns
        )
        
        self.models['LSTM'] = lstm_model
        self.predictions['LSTM'] = lstm_pred
        self.metrics['LSTM'] = lstm_metrics
        self.feature_importance['LSTM'] = lstm_importance
        
        # Store additional info for LSTM
        self.lstm_scaler = scaler
        self.test_targets['LSTM'] = y_test_seq  # Store LSTM test targets
        self.lstm_sequence_length = seq_length
        
        return lstm_model, lstm_pred, lstm_metrics

        ax3.set_title('R Score', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
        ax3.set_ylabel('R Score')
        ax3.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)
        for i, v in enumerate(results_df['R2']):
            ax3.text(i, v + max(results_df['R2'])*0.02, f'{v:.3f}', 
                    ha='center', fontweight='bold')
        
        # LSTM training history
        if 'LSTM' in self.training_history:
            ax4 = plt.subplot(2, 3, 4)
            history = self.training_history['LSTM']
            epochs = range(1, len(history['loss']) + 1)
            ax4.plot(epochs, history['loss'], 'b-', label='Training Loss', linewidth=2)
            ax4.plot(epochs, history['val_loss'], 'r-', label='Validation Loss', linewidth=2)
            ax4.axvline(x=history['best_epoch'], color='green', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7, label=f'Best Epoch ({history["best_epoch"]})')
            ax4.set_title('LSTM Training History', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
            ax4.set_xlabel('Epoch')
            ax4.set_ylabel('Loss (MSE)')
            ax4.legend()

            ax5.plot(epochs, history['val_mae'], 'r-', label='Validation MAE', linewidth=2)
            ax5.set_title('LSTM MAE History', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
            ax5.set_xlabel('Epoch')
            ax5.set_ylabel('MAE')
            ax5.legend()
            ax5.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
        
        # Model ranking comparison
        ax6 = plt.subplot(2, 3, 6)
        metrics_for_comparison = results_df[['MAE', 'RMSE', 'R2']].copy()
        # Normalize metrics (lower is better for MAE, RMSE; higher is better for R2)
        metrics_normalized = metrics_for_comparison.copy()
        metrics_normalized['MAE'] = 1 - (metrics_normalized['MAE'] / metrics_normalized['MAE'].max())
        metrics_normalized['RMSE'] = 1 - (metrics_normalized['RMSE'] / metrics_normalized['RMSE'].max())
        # R2 is already normalized (higher is better)
        
        x = np.arange(len(metrics_normalized.columns))
        width = 0.25
        
        for i, (model, scores) in enumerate(metrics_normalized.iterrows()):
            ax6.bar(x + i*width, scores.values, width, label=model, alpha=0.8)
        
        ax6.set_title('Normalized Metrics Comparison', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
        ax6.set_xticks(x + width)
        ax6.set_xticklabels(metrics_normalized.columns)
        ax6.legend()
        ax6.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)
        
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()
        
        return results_df
    
    def create_comprehensive_feature_importance_analysis(self):
        """Create comprehensive feature importance analysis for all models"""
        print("\nCOMPREHENSIVE FEATURE IMPORTANCE ANALYSIS")
        print("-" * 60)
        
        # Create figure with subplots for each model
        fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(20, 16))
        fig.suptitle('Comprehensive Feature Importance Analysis', fontsize=20, fontweight='bold')
        
        colors = ['#2E8B57', '#4169E1', '#FF6347']
        
        # Individual model importance plots
        model_names = ['Random Forest', 'XGBoost', 'LSTM']
        positions = [(0, 0), (0, 1), (1, 0)]
        
        for i, model_name in enumerate(model_names):
            if model_name in self.feature_importance:
                importance_df = self.feature_importance[model_name].head(15)
                row, col = positions[i]
                ax = axes[row, col]
                
                bars = ax.barh(range(len(importance_df)), importance_df['importance'], 
                              color=colors[i], alpha=0.8)
                ax.set_yticks(range(len(importance_df)))
                ax.set_yticklabels(importance_df['feature'], fontsize=10)
                ax.set_title(f'{model_name} - Top 15 Features', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
                ax.set_xlabel('Importance Score')
                ax.invert_yaxis()
                ax.grid(axis='x', alpha=0.3)
                
                # Add importance values on bars
                for j, (_, row) in enumerate(importance_df.iterrows()):
                    ax.text(row['importance'] + max(importance_df['importance'])*0.01, j, 
                           f'{row["importance"]:.4f}', va='center', fontsize=9)
        
        # Combined comparison plot
        ax_combined = axes[1, 1]
        
        # Get top 10 features from each model and create comparison
        all_features = set()
        for model_name in model_names:
            if model_name in self.feature_importance:
                top_features = self.feature_importance[model_name].head(10)['feature'].tolist()
                all_features.update(top_features)
        
        # Create comparison dataframe
        comparison_data = []
        for feature in all_features:
            row = {'feature': feature}
            for model_name in model_names:
                if model_name in self.feature_importance:
                    feature_row = self.feature_importance[model_name][
                        self.feature_importance[model_name]['feature'] == feature
                    ]
                    if len(feature_row) > 0:
                        row[model_name] = feature_row.iloc[0]['importance']
                    else:
                        row[model_name] = 0
                else:
                    row[model_name] = 0
            comparison_data.append(row)
        
        comparison_df = pd.DataFrame(comparison_data)
        
        # Get top features by average importance
        comparison_df['avg_importance'] = comparison_df[model_names].mean(axis=1)
        top_features = comparison_df.nlargest(10, 'avg_importance')
        
        # Create grouped bar chart
        x = np.arange(len(top_features))
        width = 0.25
        
        for i, model_name in enumerate(model_names):
            if model_name in self.feature_importance:
                ax_combined.bar(x + i*width, top_features[model_name], width, 
                               label=model_name, color=colors[i], alpha=0.8)
        
        ax_combined.set_title('Feature Importance Comparison - Top 10 Features', 
                             fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
        ax_combined.set_xlabel('Features')
        ax_combined.set_ylabel('Importance Score')
        ax_combined.set_xticks(x + width)
        ax_combined.set_xticklabels(top_features['feature'], rotation=45, ha='right')
        ax_combined.legend()
        ax_combined.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)
        
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()
        
        # Print detailed feature importance analysis
        print("\nDETAILED FEATURE IMPORTANCE RANKINGS:")
        print("=" * 60)
        
        for model_name in model_names:
            if model_name in self.feature_importance:
                print(f"\n{model_name.upper()} - TOP 10 FEATURES:")
                print("-" * 40)
                top_10 = self.feature_importance[model_name].head(10)
                for idx, row in top_10.iterrows():
                    print(f"{row['rank']:2d}. {row['feature']:<25} {row['importance']:.6f}")
        
        # Feature importance correlation analysis
        print(f"\nFEATURE IMPORTANCE CORRELATION ANALYSIS:")
        print("-" * 50)
        
        if len(model_names) >= 2:
            # Create correlation matrix of feature importance rankings
            ranking_comparison = pd.DataFrame()
            
            for model_name in model_names:
                if model_name in self.feature_importance:
                    # Create feature-rank mapping
                    feature_ranks = {}
                    for idx, row in self.feature_importance[model_name].iterrows():
                        feature_ranks[row['feature']] = row['rank']
                    
                    # Create series with all features
                    all_features_series = pd.Series(index=self.feature_names, dtype=float)
                    for feature in self.feature_names:
                        if feature in feature_ranks:
                            all_features_series[feature] = feature_ranks[feature]
                        else:
                            all_features_series[feature] = len(self.feature_names) + 1
                    
                    ranking_comparison[model_name] = all_features_series
            
            # Calculate correlations
            if len(ranking_comparison.columns) >= 2:
                correlations = ranking_comparison.corr()
                print("\nFeature Ranking Correlations (Spearman):")
                for i in range(len(correlations.columns)):
                    for j in range(i+1, len(correlations.columns)):
                        model1 = correlations.columns[i]
                        model2 = correlations.columns[j]
                        corr_val = correlations.iloc[i, j]
                        print(f"  {model1} vs {model2}: {corr_val:.3f}")
        
        return comparison_df
    
    def create_prediction_quality_analysis(self):
        """Create comprehensive prediction quality analysis plots"""
        print("\nPREDICTION QUALITY ANALYSIS")
        print("-" * 40)
        
        fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 3, figsize=(18, 15))
        fig.suptitle('Comprehensive Prediction Quality Analysis', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
        
        colors = ['#2E8B57', '#4169E1', '#FF6347']
        model_names = list(self.predictions.keys())
        
        for i, model_name in enumerate(model_names):
            # Get appropriate test targets for each model
            if model_name in self.test_targets:
                y_true = self.test_targets[model_name]
            else:
                # Fallback - should not happen with fixed implementation
                y_true = np.arange(len(self.predictions[model_name]))
            
            y_pred = self.predictions[model_name]
            
            # Ensure arrays have same length
            min_length = min(len(y_true), len(y_pred))
            y_true = y_true[:min_length]
            y_pred = y_pred[:min_length]
            
            # Row 1: Scatter plot - Predicted vs Actual
            ax1 = axes[0, i]
            ax1.scatter(y_true, y_pred, alpha=0.6, color=colors[i], s=20)
            
            # Perfect prediction line
            min_val = min(np.min(y_true), np.min(y_pred))
            max_val = max(np.max(y_true), np.max(y_pred))
            ax1.plot([min_val, max_val], [min_val, max_val], 'r--', linewidth=2, alpha=0.8)
            
            ax1.set_xlabel('Actual PM2.5')
            ax1.set_ylabel('Predicted PM2.5')
            ax1.set_title(f'{model_name}\nR = {self.metrics[model_name]["R2"]:.3f}')
            ax1.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
            
            # Row 2: Residuals plot
            ax2 = axes[1, i]
            residuals = y_true - y_pred
            ax2.scatter(y_pred, residuals, alpha=0.6, color=colors[i], s=20)
            ax2.axhline(y=0, color='r', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, alpha=0.8)
            ax2.set_xlabel('Predicted PM2.5')
            ax2.set_ylabel('Residuals')
            ax2.set_title(f'{model_name} - Residuals')
            ax2.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
            
            # Row 3: Error distribution
            ax3 = axes[2, i]
            absolute_errors = np.abs(residuals)
            ax3.hist(absolute_errors, bins=30, alpha=0.7, color=colors[i], edgecolor='black')
            ax3.axvline(x=np.mean(absolute_errors), color='red', linestyle='--', 
                       linewidth=2, label=f'Mean AE: {np.mean(absolute_errors):.2f}')
            ax3.set_xlabel('Absolute Error')
            ax3.set_ylabel('Frequency')
            ax3.set_title(f'{model_name} - Error Distribution')
            ax3.legend()
            ax3.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
        
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()
        
        # Additional analysis plots
        fig2, axes2 = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 10))
        fig2.suptitle('Advanced Prediction Quality Metrics', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
        
        # Time series comparison (first 200 points)
        ax_ts = axes2[0, 0]
        sample_size = min(200, min(len(self.predictions[model]) for model in model_names))
        
        for i, model_name in enumerate(model_names):
            y_true = self.test_targets[model_name][:sample_size]
            y_pred = self.predictions[model_name][:sample_size]
            
            if i == 0:  # Plot actual values only once
                ax_ts.plot(range(sample_size), y_true, 'k-', alpha=0.8, 
                          linewidth=2, label='Actual')
            ax_ts.plot(range(sample_size), y_pred, color=colors[i], alpha=0.7, 
                      linewidth=1.5, label=f'{model_name} Predicted')
        
        ax_ts.set_xlabel('Sample Index')
        ax_ts.set_ylabel('PM2.5 Value')
        ax_ts.set_title('Time Series Comparison (First 200 samples)')
        ax_ts.legend()
        ax_ts.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
        
        # Error magnitude comparison
        ax_error = axes2[0, 1]
        error_data = []
        model_labels = []
        
        for model_name in model_names:
            y_true = self.test_targets[model_name]
            y_pred = self.predictions[model_name]
            min_length = min(len(y_true), len(y_pred))
            errors = np.abs(y_true[:min_length] - y_pred[:min_length])
            error_data.append(errors)
            model_labels.append(model_name)
        
        ax_error.boxplot(error_data, labels=model_labels)
        ax_error.set_ylabel('Absolute Error')
        ax_error.set_title('Error Distribution Comparison')
        ax_error.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
        
        # Prediction ranges comparison
        ax_range = axes2[1, 0]
        true_ranges = []
        pred_ranges = []
        
        for model_name in model_names:

            pred_ranges.append([np.min(y_pred), np.max(y_pred)])
        
        x_pos = np.arange(len(model_names))
        width = 0.35
        
        true_mins = [r[0] for r in true_ranges]
        true_maxs = [r[1] for r in true_ranges]
        pred_mins = [r[0] for r in pred_ranges]
        pred_maxs = [r[1] for r in pred_ranges]
        
        ax_range.bar(x_pos - width/2, true_maxs, width, bottom=true_mins, 
                    label='Actual Range', alpha=0.7, color='gray')
        ax_range.bar(x_pos + width/2, pred_maxs, width, bottom=pred_mins, 
                    label='Predicted Range', alpha=0.7, color='orange')
        
        ax_range.set_xlabel('Model')
        ax_range.set_ylabel('PM2.5 Value')
        ax_range.set_title('Prediction Range Comparison')
        ax_range.set_xticks(x_pos)

        ax_range.legend()

        # Model performance radar chart
        ax_radar = axes2[1, 1]
        
        # Normalize metrics for radar chart
        metrics_df = pd.DataFrame(self.metrics).T
        normalized_metrics = {}
        
        # Normalize MAE and RMSE (lower is better - invert)
        mae_max = metrics_df['MAE'].max()
        rmse_max = metrics_df['RMSE'].max()
        
        for model in model_names:
            normalized_metrics[model] = [
                1 - (self.metrics[model]['MAE'] / mae_max),  # Inverted MAE
                1 - (self.metrics[model]['RMSE'] / rmse_max),  # Inverted RMSE
                self.metrics[model]['R2']  # R2 (higher is better)
            ]
        
        # Create radar chart
        angles = np.linspace(0, 2*np.pi, 3, endpoint=False).tolist()
        angles += angles[:1]  # Complete the circle
        
        for i, model in enumerate(model_names):
            values = normalized_metrics[model]
            values += values[:1]  # Complete the circle
            ax_radar.plot(angles, values, 'o-', linewidth=2, label=model, color=colors[i])
            ax_radar.fill(angles, values, alpha=0.25, color=colors[i])
        
        ax_radar.set_xticks(angles[:-1])
        ax_radar.set_xticklabels(['MAE (inv)', 'RMSE (inv)', 'R'])
        ax_radar.set_ylim(0, 1)
        ax_radar.set_title('Model Performance Radar Chart')
        ax_radar.legend()
        ax_radar.grid(True)
        
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()
        
        # Print detailed quality metrics
        print("\nDETAILED PREDICTION QUALITY METRICS:")
        print("=" * 60)
        
        for model_name in model_names:
            y_true = self.test_targets[model_name]
            y_pred = self.predictions[model_name]
            min_length = min(len(y_true), len(y_pred))
            y_true = y_true[:min_length]
            y_pred = y_pred[:min_length]
            
            residuals = y_true - y_pred
            abs_errors = np.abs(residuals)
            
            print(f"\n{model_name.upper()}:")
            print(f"  Test samples: {len(y_true)}")
            print(f"  Mean Absolute Error: {np.mean(abs_errors):.3f}")
            print(f"  Median Absolute Error: {np.median(abs_errors):.3f}")
            print(f"  Max Absolute Error: {np.max(abs_errors):.3f}")
            print(f"  Error Std Dev: {np.std(abs_errors):.3f}")
            print(f"  Prediction Range: [{np.min(y_pred):.2f}, {np.max(y_pred):.2f}]")
            print(f"  Actual Range: [{np.min(y_true):.2f}, {np.max(y_true):.2f}]")
            
            # Calculate percentage of predictions within certain error ranges
            within_5 = np.mean(abs_errors <= 5) * 100
            within_10 = np.mean(abs_errors <= 10) * 100
            within_20 = np.mean(abs_errors <= 20) * 100
            
            print(f"  Predictions within 5 units: {within_5:.1f}%")
            print(f"  Predictions within 10 units: {within_10:.1f}%")
            print(f"  Predictions within 20 units: {within_20:.1f}%")

# ============================================================================
# 5. ENHANCED MAIN EXECUTION PIPELINE
# ============================================================================

def main(file_path, lstm_epochs=30):
    """Enhanced main execution pipeline with proper error handling"""
    print(f"Starting Enhanced PM2.5 prediction pipeline...")
    print(f"Data file: {file_path}")
    print(f"LSTM epochs: {lstm_epochs}")
    
    # Initialize results storage
    output_dir = "/kaggle/working/model_outputs"
    os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)
    
    try:
        # Step 1: Load and assess data quality
        processor = DataProcessor(file_path)
        df = processor.load_and_assess_quality()
        df = processor.preprocess_data()
        
        # Step 2: Enhanced feature engineering
        engineer = FeatureEngineer(df)
        df_engineered = engineer.create_features()
        
        # Step 3: Prepare data for modeling
        if 'PM2.5' not in df_engineered.columns:
            print("Error: PM2.5 column not found in the dataset")
            return None, None, None
        
        # Define features and target
        target = 'PM2.5'
        exclude_cols = [target, 'year', 'month', 'day', 'hour'] + \
                      [col for col in df_engineered.columns if 'date' in col.lower()]
        features = [col for col in df_engineered.columns if col not in exclude_cols]
        
        print(f"Features selected: {len(features)}")
        print(f"Target variable: {target}")
        
        # Split data (70-30 temporal split)
        split_idx = int(0.7 * len(df_engineered))
        train_data = df_engineered.iloc[:split_idx]
        test_data = df_engineered.iloc[split_idx:]
        
        X_train = train_data[features]
        y_train = train_data[target]
        X_test = test_data[features]
        y_test = test_data[target]
        
        print(f"Training set: {len(X_train)} samples")
        print(f"Test set: {len(X_test)} samples")
        print(f"Feature dimensions: {X_train.shape[1]}")
        
        # Step 4: Train enhanced models
        trainer = EnhancedModelTrainer(X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test)
        
        print("\n4. ENHANCED MODEL TRAINING")
        print("=" * 50)
        
        # Train all models with enhanced features
        trainer.train_random_forest()
        trainer.train_xgboost()
        trainer.train_lstm(epochs=lstm_epochs)
        
        # Step 5: Enhanced visualization and analysis
        visualizer = EnhancedModelVisualizer(
            trainer.models, 
            trainer.predictions, 
            trainer.metrics,
            trainer.feature_importance,
            trainer.training_history,
            features,
            trainer.test_targets  # Pass test targets for visualization
        )
        
        results_df = visualizer.create_comprehensive_comparison()
        feature_comparison = visualizer.create_comprehensive_feature_importance_analysis()
        visualizer.create_prediction_quality_analysis()
        
        # Step 6: Save enhanced results
        print("\n6. SAVING ENHANCED RESULTS")
        print("-" * 40)
        
        # Save models
        joblib.dump(trainer.models['Random Forest'], f"{output_dir}/random_forest_model.pkl")
        trainer.models['XGBoost'].save_model(f"{output_dir}/xgboost_model.json")
        trainer.models['LSTM'].save(f"{output_dir}/lstm_model.h5")
        
        # Save scaler for LSTM
        joblib.dump(trainer.lstm_scaler, f"{output_dir}/lstm_scaler.pkl")
        
        # Save comprehensive results
        results_df.to_csv(f"{output_dir}/comprehensive_model_comparison.csv")
        feature_comparison.to_csv(f"{output_dir}/feature_importance_comparison.csv", index=False)
        
        # Save individual feature importance results
        for model_name, importance_df in trainer.feature_importance.items():
            safe_name = model_name.lower().replace(' ', '_')
            importance_df.to_csv(f"{output_dir}/{safe_name}_feature_importance.csv", index=False)
        
        # Save training history with proper JSON serialization
        if trainer.training_history:
            with open(f"{output_dir}/training_history.json", 'w') as f:
                # All values are already converted to native Python types in train_lstm
                json.dump(trainer.training_history, f, indent=2)
        
        # Save enhanced quality report
        quality_report_enhanced = processor.quality_report.copy()
        quality_report_enhanced.update({
            'total_features_engineered': int(len(features)),
            'lstm_sequence_length': int(trainer.lstm_sequence_length) if hasattr(trainer, 'lstm_sequence_length') else None,
            'lstm_epochs_trained': int(len(trainer.training_history['LSTM']['loss'])) if 'LSTM' in trainer.training_history else None,
            'lstm_best_epoch': int(trainer.training_history['LSTM']['best_epoch']) if 'LSTM' in trainer.training_history else None
        })
        
        with open(f"{output_dir}/enhanced_quality_report.json", 'w') as f:
            json.dump(quality_report_enhanced, f, indent=2)
        
        # Create detailed summary report
        summary_report = {
            'pipeline_info': {
                'execution_time': datetime.now().strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"),
                'data_file': file_path,
                'lstm_epochs': int(lstm_epochs)
            },
            'data_info': {
                'total_samples': int(len(df_engineered)),
                'training_samples': int(len(X_train)),
                'test_samples': int(len(X_test)),
                'total_features': int(len(features)),
                'missing_values_handled': int(quality_report_enhanced['missing_values'])
            },
            'model_performance': {
                model: {metric: float(value) for metric, value in metrics.items()}
                for model, metrics in trainer.metrics.items()
            },
            'best_model': {
                'name': results_df['R2'].idxmax(),
                'r2_score': float(results_df['R2'].max()),
                'mae': float(results_df.loc[results_df['R2'].idxmax(), 'MAE']),
                'rmse': float(results_df.loc[results_df['R2'].idxmax(), 'RMSE'])
            },
            'feature_importance_top5': {}
        }
        
        # Add top 5 features for each model
        for model_name, importance_df in trainer.feature_importance.items():
            summary_report['feature_importance_top5'][model_name] = [
                {
                    'feature': row['feature'],
                    'importance': float(row['importance']),
                    'rank': int(row['rank'])
                }
                for _, row in importance_df.head(5).iterrows()
            ]
        
        with open(f"{output_dir}/pipeline_summary_report.json", 'w') as f:
            json.dump(summary_report, f, indent=2)
        
        print("All enhanced models and results saved successfully!")
        
        # Enhanced final summary
        print("\n" + "=" * 80)
        print("ENHANCED FINAL SUMMARY")
        print("=" * 80)
        
        best_model = results_df['R2'].idxmax()
        best_r2 = results_df.loc[best_model, 'R2']
        best_mae = results_df.loc[best_model, 'MAE']
        best_rmse = results_df.loc[best_model, 'RMSE']
        
        print(f"Best performing model: {best_model}")
        print(f"  R score: {best_r2:.3f}")
        print(f"  MAE: {best_mae:.3f}")
        print(f"  RMSE: {best_rmse:.3f}")
        
        if 'LSTM' in trainer.training_history:
            lstm_history = trainer.training_history['LSTM']
            print(f"\nLSTM Training Details:")
            print(f"  Epochs completed: {lstm_history['epochs_trained']}")
            print(f"  Best epoch: {lstm_history['best_epoch']}")
            print(f"  Final training loss: {lstm_history['loss'][-1]:.4f}")
            print(f"  Final validation loss: {lstm_history['val_loss'][-1]:.4f}")
        
        print(f"\nTotal features engineered: {len(features)}")
        print(f"Results and analysis saved to: {output_dir}")
        
        print(f"\nTop 3 most important features across all models:")
        if feature_comparison is not None and len(feature_comparison) > 0:
            top_overall = feature_comparison.nlargest(3, 'avg_importance')
            for idx, (_, row) in enumerate(top_overall.iterrows()):
                print(f"  {idx+1}. {row['feature']} (avg importance: {row['avg_importance']:.4f})")
        
        return trainer, visualizer, results_df
        
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"Error in enhanced pipeline: {str(e)}")
        import traceback
        traceback.print_exc()
        print("\nEnhanced pipeline failed. Please check the error messages above.")
        return None, None, None
